
[1]pharmacy

   PHAR'MACY, n. [Gr. a medicament, whether salutary or poisonous.]

   The art or practice of preparing, preserving and compounding
   substances, whether vegetable, mineral or animal, for the purposes of
   medicine; the occupation of an apothecary.
